RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. (PLUS UP TO $6,600 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COPPER KAN broke alertly at the head of the pack, settled in hand to track the leaders from two wide in the second flight while patiently handled, angled out at the head of the lane and reeled in the game pacesetters in deep stretch to be going away at the wire. BRINGONTHEBUBBLY pressed the pace from two wide, exchanged bobs on the lead with RUNWAY HIT to mid-stretch, was passed late by the winner and the show horse but battled back gamely near the wire to garner the place. RUNWAY HIT sped up the fence to duel on the lead shortly from the gate, battled willingly on the lead to deep stretch, could not hold off the winner and surrendered the place in the final strides in a good effort. TAPITSGOTAPISTOL broke with the field, dropped to race in the back pair and never menaced. COUNTRY VISION trailed in the back pair and never was a threat. SHEZ DA BEEZ KNEEZ chased the pace from the rail in the second flight and faded turning for home.

ENTRY.NAME: Shez Da Beez Kneez
ENTRY.OWNER: Caldwell, J. R. and Mojo Racing Partners
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside, through early, faded

ENTRY.NAME: Copper Kan
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke alertly, settled, angled 3w, closed well, going away

ENTRY.NAME: Tapitsgotapistol
ENTRY.COMMENT: dropped back, never menaced

ENTRY.NAME: Country Vision
ENTRY.COMMENT: trailed, evenly, no threat,

ENTRY.NAME: Runway Hit
ENTRY.COMMENT: speed, dueled inside, led, willingly, caught late

ENTRY.NAME: Bringonthebubbly
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, dueled, gamely, determined, up for place

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 2 1M Turf CR: 93. Allowance Purse 33500. (PLUS UP TO $6,700 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TEXAS BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since April 16, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRES SOLES tracked the pace while being well rated along the inside throughout the first three quarters, then was urging on the far turn, dug in gamely in the early stretch and rushed to the wire to prove best. READY TO ROLL chased the pace from the inside into the first turn and into the second turn, then gained command in the early stretch and was closing gamely but was outkicked in the end by an inner rival and was second best. COLOR FAST saved ground while racing behind the field throughout the backstretch, was gaining steadily on the far turn from the three path, then rallied in the upper stretch and was closing strong in the end. HOLY EMPEROR stalked the pace while two wide, then menaced throughout the far bend and into the early stretch then gave way in the end. SUMMER LOVER settled in the two path down the backstretch, then came out four wide on the far turn to rally in the late stretch but came up empty. MANOR BORN settled along the inside throughout the backstretch, then bid on the far turn to close well in the stretch but it wasn't enough. EXETER chased the pace while three wide on the backstretch, was in a hard drive throughout the far turn then continued to close gamely in the home stretch but it wasn't enough. CANATLAN set the pace into the first turn, then lead the way into the second turn under a steady hand ride, then faltered in the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Manor Born
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled inside, bid far turn, closed well, not enough

ENTRY.NAME: Ready to Roll
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside, bid2w far turn, lead upper, outkicked late

ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, gaining 3w far turn, 5wupper, closed strong

ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace inside, steady hand ride, faltered stretch

ENTRY.COMMENT: settled 2 wide, 4 wide far turn, rallied late, empty

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalk 2 wide, menace 3 wide stretch, gave way late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 89. Allowance Purse 34500. (PLUS UP TO $1,725 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TRIAL OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FEARLESS PRINCE pressed the pace from shortly out of the gate, dueled from two wide with the runner-up, repelled early challenges at the quarter pole and out-finished the pacesetter late in the lane to draw clear. WILL THE THRILL sped to the lead along the fence, dueled with the winner to mid-stretch while separating from the rest of the field but was out-finished late in the lane. SILENCE D'ORO raced up the fence just off the early lead, could not establish a rail position and was forced to steady behind the two dueling leaders repeatedly for over a quarter mile while unable to find room between horses or on the fence, angled out at the top of the lane and finished willingly. STANS HOME RUN dropped to nearly the tail of the field shortly from the gate and showed mild late interest rallying in the stretch. MY GOLDEN M reared as the gates opened spotting the field several lengths, rushed up five wide to be prominent in the turn and flattened out coming home. TAPITS KASH well placed early on but lacked a response when called upon in the turn. TEXAS GOLD RUSH trailed and was never a threat.

ENTRY.COMMENT: steadied repeatedly, lacked racing room, angled out, closed well

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 4 5F Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. (PLUS UP TO $6,600 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLING DANCER vied for the lead while four wide, was in a steady drive to gain the lead leaving the turn, then held on well down the stretch to succeed in the end. ALL AMERICAN LADY chased the pace while three wide, then was urging steadily throughout the bend to gain second position, continued to rally in the stretch but could not catch the leader in the end. SHAKE THOSE DICE raced behind the field into the turn, then angled out four wide, dug in gamely in the early stretch and closed willingly. DULCE AMANECER YG vied for the lead while three wide, then settled back on the turn, then re rallied in the stretch to close well in the end. TEXACANA chased the pace while two wide, then settled back throughout the turn to rebid in the upper stretch from the five path but was no threat. CREAM PUFF REAPER vied for the lead from the inside, was in a strong drive throughout the bend then gave way on the stretch. CRESSONS LIL CHARM was fractious in the gate after being reloaded, then vied between rivals under a hard drive into the turn then flattened out in the stretch. LITTLE ELLIE sat in the gate prior to the start and had to be reloaded, then chased the pace from the inside into the turn and did not respond in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 5 5F Turf CR: 83. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 33500. (PLUS UP TO $6,700 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $50,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main trac k at Five Furlongs.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BYE sped to the lead from between horses to duel to head of the lane, shook clear of the pace pressers to open a clear advantage and held the closer safe to the line. DARK AFTERNOON unhurried in the early going, rallied midway on the turn circling six wide to mount a fast closing rally and came up two strides short. AARON'S SPIRIT settled off the pace from between horses, responded when called upon and finished well in the lane. WILL TAKE CASH sent up the rail for the early lead, dueled from the fence under constant pressure to upper stretch and weakened deep in the drive. TUNGSTEN saved ground along the fence racing at the head of the second flight, threatened turning for home and flattened out down the stretch. TOO MUCH INFO tracked the leaders while well positioned two wide, raced with head cocked to the inside around the turn and lacked a response when called upon turning for home. RODEO CHAMP trailed most of the way and passed tiring rivals in the lane. DOSE'S DREAM went evenly as no threat. MUD ON MY BOOTS used early to be prompting the pace from three wide into the turn and came up empty.

PROUD VALENTINE chased the pace while three wide then angled in on the turn to bid from the two path into the stretch then gave way in the end. BLING ON THE LIGHT raced behind field while two wide, was urging on the turn to try and gain second position but gave way in the end. A SONG FOR MICKEY chased the pace while two wide, then dropped back heading into the turn and stopped.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 7 1M Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 12500. (PLUS UP TO $2,500 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAJOR CONTENDER stalked the pace from three wide into the turn, took the lead at the quarter pole, was headed in mid-stretch by the runner-up and fought back gamely to prevail at the wire. KISS PRINCIPAL settled near the rear of the field in the early going, steadily gained ground down the backstretch, rallied five wide in the turn to engage the leaders, rider lost whip leaving the quarter pole, overtook the leader in mid-stretch but was out-finished late in the lane. DENS DEVILLE rated in mid-pack to the head of the stretch, angled out and made a good belated rally to be gaining late. VICTOR VALENTINO unhurried for the first half mile, gained ground in the turn to threaten in upper stretch and finished evenly. GIST slow early to trail, gained some ground in the turn and passed weakening rivals down the lane. BIG STORY bobbled slightly leaving the gate, moved up entering the first turn to press the pace and weakened turning for home. SOMEBODY IN TEXAS took control of the pace into the first turn, set a pressured pace down the backside and retreated through the stretch. BRAZIL NUT went evenly and was never a threat. PLUTONIUM well placed for the first half mile and came up empty.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 8 1M Turf CR: 63. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. (PLUS UP TO $1,650 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For $20,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts). (If Deemed inadvisable by managemen t to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IBERIAN RUNNER tracked the pace while being well rated along the inside, was moving up on the second turn, gained command mid stretch then held on to prove best in the end. TEAM GORMLEY dueled for the lead from the inside throughout the first three quarters, was in a long drive heading into the stretch, continued to rally gamely and held onto the place prize in the end. KING ARTHUR RIDGE settled along the inside under a steady hand ride from the first turn and into the second then rallied in late stretch to close gamely for the show prize. EAGLEFORD tracked the pace while two wide down the backstretch, was gaining swiftly on the far turn then closed willingly in the stretch. JOHN LOUIS' BEVO settled in the two path, then made a mild bid on the far turn and came up evenly in the stretch. TEXAN FARMER raced in the middle of the pack while three wide, was urging on the far turn to vie for the lead heading into the home stretch then gave way in the end. MODOC was unhurried early, then raced behind the field, bid on the far turn from the inside and was no threat. GOD'S GOLD was unhurried early then raced in the four path in the back of the pack, made a mild bid on the far turn and into the home stretch and was no threat. SECOND BATTALION dueled while two wide down the backstretch and into the far turn, was in a hard drive, then was used up and weakened in the stretch.
